text: The Medog ridge-nosed tree frog (Nasutixalus medogensis) is a frog. It lives in Tibet, in China. People have seen it 1619 meters above sea level. This frog lives high in the trees where the branches come together like a roof. Scientists think human beings changing wetlands could hurt this frog. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Nasutixalus medogensis
